1. We spent some time looking at an example of a _public cloud_ service, AWS. Running operations on 
a pulic cloud is an easy, cost-effective way to provide services.

2. Recall the three main components of cloud services:
  - Compute
  - Storage
  - Network

3. Sometimes an organsation's needs are better met by running a _private cloud_ service. This means that you will need to supply the three service above, plus some other services for managing th ewhole thing.

4. Also, recall that, with AWS we had web based and command line tools as well as a service API.  We may want to offer these in our private clouds.

5. So the first big thing to take away is that setting up and running a private cloud is a lot of work.  Do not elect to do this lightly.

